Rating: 3
Delicious.. Jeff the cook concerned about all the cream needn't be so concerned. The cream and cheese both highlighted the carrots without masking their flavor. I also cut the amount of carrots down to 2 lbs instead of 4 and the proportions seemed fine. I can't imagine using the entire amount that's called for. Julienning the carrots makes a pretty presentation. The corn stuffing topping was a perfect crunchy balance to the creamy carrots. Will definitely make it again.

Rating: 2
I have no problem using fat to enrich a dish, but a full cup of cream and quite a bit of cheese didn't add anything meaningful to this. I suppose if one is trying to mask the flavor of the carrots in the way people sometimes drown broccoli in cheese sauce, this recipe may be a good way to get kids to eat their vegetables. Not me though. If you insist on making these, do your heart a favor and use milk instead of cream.

Rating: 4
I made this a few weeks ago and it was a huge hit. Four of us devoured it all. Going to make it again tonight too. A delicious and different way to prepare carrots.

Rating: 3
This is oh so tasty, and very pretty (I julienned the carrots instead of cutting into rounds). The carrot taste is clear and distinctive. Despite cheese sauce, this is not a heavy dish. We served with ham, green salad and crusty bread; made a perfect light dinner. IMO, not special enough for company, but great for regular meals. A Note: the recipe calls for 4 lbs. of carrots; I used a 2 lb. bag of baby carrots and it completely filled a 13X9X2 dish. Can't imagine using more.

Rating: 4
A geat vegetable dish for a gathering at Easter or anytime. My son in law like it and he said he doesn't normally like carrots! I made it ahead and left only the baking until the serving day. Makes too much for just two but is great for a crowd and leftovers taste good. Anyone concerned with too much fat could easily substitute low fat cheese and milk for the cheese and cream.

Rating: 3
This is now my boyfriend's favorite carrot dish. I used seasoned bread crumbs instead of stuffing mix and it was fine. Definitely needs the celery and onions. Very tasty.